description.text:
It's quite unoriginal as quadcopters go.  It has four arms that join at the  shoulders and mount motors at their ends.  It's designed to bolt together and mount a KK multicopter board.  
The parts were printed in PLA; .3 mm layer, 15% infill.  
The motors used in this particular build are from Hobby King - &quot;www.hobbyking.com/hobbyking/store/<strong >6744</strong>AD_100L_Micro_Brushless_Outrunner_1850Kv.html&quot;  
ESCs are also from Hobby King - &quot;www.hobbyking.com/hobbyking/store/<strong >4318</strong>TURNIGY_Plush_6A_8bec_6g_Speed_Controller.html&quot;  
